texts.text: >Somewhere in Europe...
Yes, I see...
>A man scribbles notes while looking at a star map.
No, this cannot be. It does not match my predictions. Why?
This... This has to be...
>He starts performing calculations while looking at old books and notes...
I-It's this...!! If this truly is what it means...!!
Two weeks... It will happen in two weeks...!
In two weeks, the stars will align perfectly...!
No, we don't have time for that!
I must spread the word! I must tell everyone I can!
Y'all asked me if you could use the livin' room,
and I said yes, right?
But I wasn't expectin' y'all to do this, yo...
>The Hideout's living room is littered with papers and files...
This is incredible.
Where do we walk?
And y'all are the ones behind this mess?
You say that as if we're criminals.
Did I not ask to borrow this space to look at some files?
Yo, Kazufumi, look up "some" in the dictionary next time you get a chance...
My apologies. I'm the one who originally asked Kazufumi to help with this.
I understand that it may seem strange that we're working together like this.
What are you doing?
Did something happen?
A few days ago, I received a letter from an old friend...
Unfortunately, I couldn't understand a word of it.
I've spent several days trying to figure it out to no avail.
That was when I decided to ask Kazufumi.
Some kind of mystery letter and Kazufumi...
Yo, does that mean some kind of demon's involved here?
Sadly, we don't even know that much.
We did however come to the conclusion that it's a chant for a ritual of some sort.
Which is why I asked to see if he'd seen anything like this before...
As far as I could tell, it was pure gibberish,
but there was one thing that caught my attention...
A part of me believed that this was written down and in my possession somewhere.
Yo, now I get it. The researcher in you's all obsessed about it now.
Would you like to see it as well?
Aight, why not? Ain't no harm in lookin', right?
It's this...
The stars will align, but only for a moment. In perfect position or very close to it.
My dear friends, you will understand, that I am certain.
This planet's ruler of old has spoken.
Do not fear. Do not deny it. Your eyes have not yet opened.
Knowing the unknown is but a terrible notion.
But fear not I say, for you have been chosen.
Now, you must open your eyes that have been shut.
Be witness to it and you will know what!
Then we will grow closer than ever before.
That is when you will know what this was all for...
Rejoice! All hail the great Cthulhu!

Ia! Ia!
Cthulhu fhtagn!
Yo, what the hell's goin' on...?
It's pure nonsense.
Ia.. Ia... What?
Yes, an honest response.
Yeah, that last part. Yo, how the hell do you read that?
Cu...? No, Cthu...? Start by pronouncin' the "C", I guess?
It looks like it's written in English but...
Hey, Vagit! What language is this in?
Yes, that last part is the most troubling indeed.
I've tried looking at other languages but nothing.
I also translated as much as I could so that Kazufumi could read it.
But there was nothing I could do about that word, so I left it as is.
Is it a code?
Cthulhu...?
A code... Yes, that is a possibility.
Yo, it doesn't make any sense like this. What if it's like a code?
Ain't this one of those code-cracking riddles that folks have been talkin' about?
Or maybe it's too occult for that.
Yo, Shiang Sun would love seein' somethin' like this...
But he said he's gonna be busy writin' a report for a while.
Then why don't we think on this in the meantime?
I don't see why not. It's not as if we have anything to work with right now.
But it could very well be a silly puzzle he made on a whim.
Yet, he really isn't the type to do anything like this...
So what's he like? Yo, he's your friend, right?
He's very knowledgeable and one who's dabbled in quite a few fields.
Archaeology, anthropology, astronomy... It was one thing after another with him.
He had a talent for connecting completely unrelated matters together.
That was when he was at his happiest.
Yo, this some kind of challenge from him then?
I mean, it looks like a real head-scratcher.
But it's also supposed to be fun, no?
Yeah, it ain't a game if it ain't fun.
Let's start by tryin' a simple Caesar cipher.
>Several hours later...
Yo, this is hopeless... Nothin' we've done's worked...!
I'm gettin' way too into this. This might be a good place to stop for today.
Yes, I agree. We may need to start looking at other reference material as well.
Thanks a bunch, Newbie!
Yo, it's gettin' pretty late. It's all good if you crash here tonight.
I'll do that.
Thank you.
Then I'll get everything ready.
But my head... It feels so heavy for some reason...
Yo, same. Maybe we pushed our brains too hard.
>You also feel a slight headache coming and close your eyes.
Huh? Yo, [sys user_name].
Don't just fall asleep on the floor like that... Hey, you listenin'...?
I'm back... Oh, asleep already...?
>Your mind slowly begins to drift away...
Fine... I'll just... Carry...
Sure... Let me... Help...

...bie! Hey, Newbie!
Wake up!
>You wake up, but feel cold and have a terrible headache.
Yo, finally. You actually awake this time?
But thank goodness, or that's what I'd like to say...
Where are we...?
I fell asleep and...
We're not sure either. We all went to sleep at the Hideout and...
When I came to, this is where we all were.
I have no idea how we got here or why we're even here.
What about the others?
Can we call anyone?
No, we don't seem to be able to, and no one else appears to be with us.
Yo, no signal at all. I thought we were screwed but...
>You then look down at your own phone.
>You see something strange where signal strength is usually indicated.
>It's as if an ominous presence has taken it over.
Yo, you okay...?
What are you droppin' your phone for all the sudden?
Sure, we got no signal, but you still need it to protect yourself.
>You look at its screen while you try to pick it up.
>You see an "X" by the signal strength antenna...
Was that real...?
Am I seeing things...?
[sys user_name], are you alright? You don't look very well.
I suppose that should be expected. We still have no idea what's happened to us,
and a place like this is definitely not for everyone.
But this could also be a clue of some kind.
It may even help us with learning how to escape this place.
This may be the definition of "fear of the unknown"...
And I have more bad news...!
I sense demons nearby... Several in fact...
Yo, seriously? What the hell is this place?
You two fight them like you usually do.
We'll try to stay out of your way as much as possible.
Aight, got it.
Let's go... Don't give 'em an inch.
